title: District 3 tennis roundup: Central York sweeps into Class AAA team quarterfinals
text:
District 3 tennis roundup: Central York sweeps into Class AAA team quarterfinals Central York rolls to a 5-0 victory vs. Governor Mifflin in Class AAA play 
GameTimePA.com Posted: 10/15/2015 09:03:43 PM EDT 
Yvonne Peters-Washington and Maddison Mummert dropped a combined two games at Nos. 1 and 2 singles, respectively, leading Central York to a 5-0 victory against Governor Mifflin in the first round of the District 3 Class AAA team tennis tournament at Hershey Racquet Club on Thursday. 
The victory propels the sixth-seeded Panthers to the quarterfinals where they will meet No. 3 seeded Cumberland Valley Tuesday back at Hershey Racquet Club. 
Jen Elder notched the third singles victory for Central, winning 6-3, 2-6, 10-4 at No. 3. The doubles teams of Sarah Conner and Sophie Brink and Kara Holland and Lily Richwine secured the sweep for Central. Conner-Brink won 3-6, 6-3, 10-8 at No. 1 while Holland and Richwine won 7-5, 6-0 at No. 2. at Hershey Racquet Club 
Singles — Yvonne Peters-Washington, CY, def. Ariana Chuprinsky, 6-0, 6-1. Maddison Mummert, CY, def. Monique White, 6-1, 6-0. Jen Elder, CY, def. Lauren Leibovitz, 6-3, 2-6, 10-4. 
Doubles — Sarah Conner-Sophie Brink, CY, def. Sumitra Jagadesan-Sarah Kerr, 3-6, 6-3, 10-8. Kara Holland-Lily Richwine, CY, def. Nicole Heath-Hannah Ramsbottom, 7-5, 6-0. 
LAMPETER-STRASBURG 3, SOUTH WESTERN 1 >> Taylor Capoferri and Sarah Capoferri won at Nos. 1 and 2 singles to lead Lampeter-Strasburg past South Western in the first round of the District 3 Class AAA team tennis tournament at Hershey Racquet Club. Advertisement 
The No. 2 doubles duo of Isabeele Mazaheri and Larson Kessler won 6-0, 6-0 for the Pioneers, who advance to face top seeded Exeter Township in Tuesday's quarterfinal. The lone Mustang victory came at No. 3 singles as Regan Ford defeated Shirley Drot de Gourville, 6-1, 6-1. at Hershey Racquet Club 
Singles — Taylor Capoferri, LS, def. Madison Bortner, 6-0, 6-0. Sarah Capoferri, LS, def. Michaela Sentz, 6-3, 6-3. Regan Ford, SW, def. Shirley Drot de Gourville, 6-1, 6-1. 
Doubles — Lauren Rettew-Sami Williams, LS, led Brooke Treadway-Sabrina Lam, 7-5, 2-2 (DNF). Isabelle Mazaheri-Larson Kessler, LS, def. Paige Rudisill-Emily Newton, 6-0, 6-0.
